Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Kenneth L Quinn-Jones in court with attorney Michael B Plaisted.  Defendant Kenneth L Quinn-Jones in custody.  Katherine M Halopka-Ivery appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 

Probation having been revoked, sentencing proceeded.  Statements by each counsel and defendant.  The court sentenced defendant to serve 90  days in the House of Correction , credit for 90 days time served. 
Court ordered all mandatory costs, fees and surcharges waived due to low income.   
Information on Postconviction Relief received and filed.

Deputy court clerk:  vk  Examiner finds that the defendant is competent to proceed.  Parties stipulate to the competency findings.   Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 47.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for April 19, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Kenneth L Quinn-Jones in court with attorney Michael B Plaisted.  Defendant Kenneth L Quinn-Jones in custody.  Katherine M Halopka-Ivery appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 

 Competency hearing proceeded.  Sworn in for the State:  Dr. Jenna Niess.  Exhibit 1 received.  State rests. Defense rests. Testimony closed .. Cause argued.   Court finds that the defendant is incompetent to proceed at this time, but if provided with appropriate treatment, is likely to become competent within 90 days  or within the maximum sentence specified for the most serious offense, whichever is less.  The proceedings are suspended.  The defendant is commited on 1-25-2016  to the Department of Health and Family Services for an indeterminate term not to exceed 90 days , or the maximum sentence specified for the most serious offense, whichever is less.      Defendant's credit on this case already exceeds the Maximum  period of incarceration.     DHFS shall designate the mental health institute.  The sheriff shall transport the defendant  FORTHWITH  to and from the designated institute.  Order of commitment for Treatment (Incompetency) signed and filed.
